# Applescript Music Data
# AppleScript can interact with the Music app on macOS to access various
# data fields associated with tracks. For example, you can retrieve
# properties such as the artist, album, genre, year, duration, and more.
# To explore the available properties, you can use the Script Editor to
# check the Library or query the properties of the current track using
# AppleScript code.
# Some of the data fields that can be accessed include:
Artist: The name of the artist associated with the track.
Album: The name of the album the track belongs to.
Genre: The genre of the track.
Year: The year the track was released.
Duration: The length of the track in seconds.
Track Number: The position of the track within the album.
Album Artist: The artist of the album, which may differ from the track artist.
Composer: The composer of the track.
Bit Rate: The bit rate of the audio file.
Sample Rate: The sample rate of the audio file.
Size: The file size of the track.
Date Added: The date the track was added to the library.
Time: The duration of the track in a formatted string.
# Additionally, there are other fields such as 
